this way use grep ,work good in cygwin grep and ubuntu
but not good in unxUtils

doc:
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/6573633/how-to-grep-a-string-in-all-the-java-files-in-subdirectories

+------------------------------------------+-----------------------+
|   e   |recursive	                       |     non-recursive     |
+-------+----------------------------------+-----------------------+
|   *   |grep -r --include=* $word $path   | grep $word $path/*    |
|   *.c |grep -r --include=*.c $word $path | grep $word $path/*.c  |
|   a.c |grep -r --include=a.c $word $path | grep $word $path/a.c  |
+------+----------------------------------+-----------------------+

